t: To the chief Musician on Neginoth, A Psalm or Song.
God*p be merciful unto us, and bless us; and cause his face to shine upon us; Selah.
That*p thy way may be known upon earth, thy saving health among all nations.
Let*p the people praise thee, O God; let all the people praise thee.
O*p let the nations be glad and sing for joy: for thou shalt judge the people righteously, and govern the nations upon earth. Selah.
Let*p the people praise thee, O God; let all the people praise thee.
Then*p shall the earth yield her increase; and God, even our own God, shall bless us.
God*p shall bless us; and all the ends of the earth shall fear him.
